    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Dissolve half the&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[whole]</span>&nbsp;<strong>stock cube</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span>&nbsp;boiled water in a heatproof bowl&nbsp;</p> <p>Add the <strong>couscous</strong> to the stock, cover and set aside&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-lime-glazed-chicken-on-couscous/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely discarding the root end<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p> <p>Set aside a small pinch of chopped spring onions for garnish</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-lime-glazed-chicken-on-couscous/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken</strong> to a bowl with the<strong>&nbsp;spring onion</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and the remaining<strong> stock cube</strong></p> <p>Mix very well and set aside</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-lime-glazed-chicken-on-couscous/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Roll the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice!) and cut in half</p> <p>Combine the juice of half a&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[whole]</span> <strong>lime</strong> with the<strong> saffron</strong> and <strong>honey</strong> - this is your glaze</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-lime-glazed-chicken-on-couscous/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken</strong> mixture and cook for 5-7 min or until cooked through</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-lime-glazed-chicken-on-couscous/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p> <p>Fluff the couscous, add the chopped <strong>coriander</strong>&nbsp;and the juice of the remaining&nbsp;<strong>lime</strong></p> <p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir in a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-lime-glazed-chicken-on-couscous/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, add a small splash of <strong>water</strong> to the pan and stir (this makes a little&nbsp;extra sauce)</p> <p>Remove the chicken from the heat</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-lime-glazed-chicken-on-couscous/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the chicken over the couscous and drizzle the saffron lime glaze over&nbsp;</p> <p>Garnish with the reserved <strong>spring onion</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
